This paper deals with the automatic evaluation of dialogue systems, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of neural networks for this task, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also explores the limitations of the ADEM model, which involves analyzing the behavior of a complex system, a topic that falls under the category of control theory (cs.NE) and systems and control (cs.SI).
